	   <tr><td colspan=2>For all those thinking verant had this dropping from an unkillable mob, you are sadly mistaken.&nbsp;&nbsp;The problem with seru at first was that you could get to him, not that he was unkillable (silly verant hadn't finished the key quest yet).  So people used CoH and grav flux to get to the top of Seru's Arx and could drop their melee down in, to fight him, while avoiding adds/guards in the room by having the casters stay up top.  Seru dropped some very nice gear compared to other stuff that had been seen at the time.  Verant considered getting to Seru to be the exploit and when they redid the encounter making it much harder, they nerfed all the existing seru drops to that like you see above.  Verant didn't put this as loot on the mob, they just got mad when someone got to the mob and killed it before they got around to finishing the key (or fixing it?)quest.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
